creator: Joseph Ashby-Sterry
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 12 recordings of A Christmas Duet by Joseph Ashby-Sterry. This was the Weekly Poetry project for December 20, 2015. Read in English by Bruce Kachuk; Brian Lornie; Beth Thomas & Jennifer Fournier; Claudia Salto; Laurie Anne Walden & David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Garth Burton; Greg Giordano & Maria Kasper; Sonia & John Burlinson; Lee Ann Howlett and Ruth Golding. Joseph Ashby-Sterry was an English poet and novelist. He works include Boudoir Ballads, a collection of poetry, now out of print. This poem is taken from the 1888 edition of The Lazy Minstrel. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B Audiobook (11MB)
